The paper deals with key generation over a non-authenticated public channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of linear programming to check the simulatability condition suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE). Finally, the use of probability mass functions and joint distributions suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
